1 /*
2 ** ###################################################################
3 ** Processors: MK20DN512ZVLK10
4 ** MK20DX256ZVLK10
5 ** MK20DN512ZVLL10
6 ** MK20DX256ZVLL10
7 ** MK20DN512ZVLQ10
8 ** MK20DX128ZVLQ10
9 ** MK20DX256ZVLQ10
10 ** MK20DN512ZVMB10
11 ** MK20DX256ZVMB10
12 ** MK20DN512ZVMC10
13 ** MK20DX256ZVMC10
14 ** MK20DN512ZVMD10
15 ** MK20DX256ZVMD10
16 ** MK20DX128ZVMD10
17 **
18 ** Compilers: Freescale C/C++ for Embedded ARM
19 ** GNU ARM C Compiler
20 ** IAR ANSI C/C++ Compiler for ARM
21 **
22 ** Reference manual: K20P144M100SF2RM, Rev. 5, 8 May 2011
23 ** Version: rev. 1.1, 2011-06-15
24 **
25 ** Abstract:
26 ** This header file implements peripheral memory map for MK20DZ10
27 ** processor.
28 **
29 ** Copyright: 1997 - 2011 Freescale Semiconductor, Inc. All Rights Reserved.
30 **
31 ** http: www.freescale.com
32 ** mail: support@freescale.com
33 **
34 ** Revisions:
35 ** - rev. 1.0 (2011-03-30)
36 ** Initial version.
37 ** Changes with respect to the previous MK10NxxVMD100 header file:
38 ** RTC - CCR register removed. Replaced by IER register.
39 ** CRC - added CTRLHU register for 8-bit access to the CTRL register.
40 ** FB - bit FB_CSCR_EXALE renamed to FB_CSCR_EXTS.
41 ** SIM- bit group FSIZE in SIM_FCFG1 split into groups PFSIZE and NVMSIZE.
42 ** Added registers for core modules - CoreDebug, DWT, ETB, ETF, ETM, FPB, ITM, TPIU.
43 ** - rev. 1.1 (2011-06-15)
44 ** Registers updated according to the new reference manual revision - Rev. 5, 8 May 2011
45 ** I2S - bit SSIEN in I2S_CR register renamed to I2SEN.
46 ** SDHC - bit VOLTSEL in SDHC_VENDOR register removed.
47 ** TSI - registers TSI_CNTR1 to TSI_CNTR15, bit group CNTN renamed to CTN1, bit group CNTN1 renamed to CTN.
48 **
49 ** ###################################################################
50 */
51

6134 typedef struct FTM_MemMap {
6135  uint32_t SC;
6136  uint32_t CNT;
6137  uint32_t MOD;
6138  struct { /* offset: 0xC, array step: 0x8 */
6139  uint32_t CnSC;
6140  uint32_t CnV;
6141  } CONTROLS[8];
6142  uint32_t CNTIN;
6143  uint32_t STATUS;
6144  uint32_t MODE;
6145  uint32_t SYNC;
6146  uint32_t OUTINIT;
6147  uint32_t OUTMASK;
6148  uint32_t COMBINE;
6149  uint32_t DEADTIME;
6150  uint32_t EXTTRIG;
6151  uint32_t POL;
6152  uint32_t FMS;
6153  uint32_t FILTER;
6154  uint32_t FLTCTRL;
6155  uint32_t QDCTRL;
6156  uint32_t CONF;
6157  uint32_t FLTPOL;
6158  uint32_t SYNCONF;
6159  uint32_t INVCTRL;
6160  uint32_t SWOCTRL;
6161  uint32_t PWMLOAD;
6162 } volatile *FTM_MemMapPtr;

8406 typedef struct MPU_MemMap {
8407  uint32_t CESR;
8408  uint8_t RESERVED_0[12];
8409  struct { /* offset: 0x10, array step: 0x8 */
8410  uint32_t EAR;
8411  uint32_t EDR;
8412  } SP[5];

8414  uint32_t WORD[12][4];
8415  uint8_t RESERVED_2[832];
8416  uint32_t RGDAAC[12];
8417 } volatile *MPU_MemMapPtr;

9342 typedef struct PDB_MemMap {
9343  uint32_t SC;
9344  uint32_t MOD;
9345  uint32_t CNT;
9346  uint32_t IDLY;
9347  struct { /* offset: 0x10, array step: 0x28 */
9348  uint32_t C1;
9349  uint32_t S;
9350  uint32_t DLY[2];
9351  uint8_t RESERVED_0[24];
9352  } CH[2];
9353  uint8_t RESERVED_0[240];
9354  struct { /* offset: 0x150, array step: 0x8 */
9355  uint32_t INTC;
9356  uint32_t INT;
9357  } DAC[2];
9358  uint8_t RESERVED_1[48];
9359  uint32_t POEN;
9360  uint32_t PODLY;
9361 } volatile *PDB_MemMapPtr;

11609  -- SPI
11610  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
11611 
11618 typedef struct SPI_MemMap {
11619  uint32_t MCR;
11620  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
11621  uint32_t TCR;
11622  union { /* offset: 0xC */
11623  uint32_t CTAR[2];
11624  uint32_t CTAR_SLAVE[1];
11625  };
11626  uint8_t RESERVED_1[24];
11627  uint32_t SR;
11628  uint32_t RSER;
11629  union { /* offset: 0x34 */
11630  uint32_t PUSHR;
11631  uint32_t PUSHR_SLAVE;
11632  };
11633  uint32_t POPR;
11634  uint32_t TXFR0;
11635  uint32_t TXFR1;
11636  uint32_t TXFR2;
11637  uint32_t TXFR3;
11638  uint8_t RESERVED_2[48];
11639  uint32_t RXFR0;
11640  uint32_t RXFR1;
11641  uint32_t RXFR2;
11642  uint32_t RXFR3;
11643 } volatile *SPI_MemMapPtr;

13502 typedef struct USB_MemMap {
13503  uint8_t PERID;
13504  uint8_t RESERVED_0[3];
13505  uint8_t IDCOMP;
13506  uint8_t RESERVED_1[3];
13507  uint8_t REV;
13508  uint8_t RESERVED_2[3];
13509  uint8_t ADDINFO;
13510  uint8_t RESERVED_3[3];
13511  uint8_t OTGISTAT;
13512  uint8_t RESERVED_4[3];
13513  uint8_t OTGICR;
13514  uint8_t RESERVED_5[3];
13515  uint8_t OTGSTAT;
13516  uint8_t RESERVED_6[3];
13517  uint8_t OTGCTL;
13518  uint8_t RESERVED_7[99];
13519  uint8_t ISTAT;
13520  uint8_t RESERVED_8[3];
13521  uint8_t INTEN;
13522  uint8_t RESERVED_9[3];
13523  uint8_t ERRSTAT;
13524  uint8_t RESERVED_10[3];
13525  uint8_t ERREN;
13526  uint8_t RESERVED_11[3];
13527  uint8_t STAT;
13528  uint8_t RESERVED_12[3];
13529  uint8_t CTL;
13530  uint8_t RESERVED_13[3];
13531  uint8_t ADDR;
13532  uint8_t RESERVED_14[3];
13533  uint8_t BDTPAGE1;
13534  uint8_t RESERVED_15[3];
13535  uint8_t FRMNUML;
13536  uint8_t RESERVED_16[3];
13537  uint8_t FRMNUMH;
13538  uint8_t RESERVED_17[3];
13539  uint8_t TOKEN;
13540  uint8_t RESERVED_18[3];
13541  uint8_t SOFTHLD;
13542  uint8_t RESERVED_19[3];
13543  uint8_t BDTPAGE2;
13544  uint8_t RESERVED_20[3];
13545  uint8_t BDTPAGE3;
13546  uint8_t RESERVED_21[11];
13547  struct { /* offset: 0xC0, array step: 0x4 */
13548  uint8_t ENDPT;
13549  uint8_t RESERVED_0[3];
13550  } ENDPOINT[16];
13551  uint8_t USBCTRL;
13552  uint8_t RESERVED_22[3];
13553  uint8_t OBSERVE;
13554  uint8_t RESERVED_23[3];
13555  uint8_t CONTROL;
13556  uint8_t RESERVED_24[3];
13557  uint8_t USBTRC0;
13558 } volatile *USB_MemMapPtr;
